HEADWORD: Scolecite
<hw>Scol"e*cite</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>skw`lhx</grk>, <grk>-hkos</grk>, a worm, earthworm.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A zeolitic mineral occurring in delicate
radiating groups of white crystals. It is a hydrous silicate of alumina
and lime. Called also <altname>lime mesotype</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scolecomorpha</ent>⟦br⟧
